      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">SOWPODS-Only Words (20 Additional)</h2>

      <p>If you play with the international Collins Scrabble Words dictionary (SOWPODS), you have access to 20 additional 2-letter words not found in the TWL. These are particularly useful in international tournaments.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">20</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Extra SOWPODS Words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">ZO (11)</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Highest Extra Word</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20">
          <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">SOWPODS-Only (A–G)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CH (7) · DA (3) · DI (3) · EA (2) · EE (2) · GI (3) · GU (3)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20">
          <p class="text-purple-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">SOWPODS-Only (I–Z)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">IO (2) · JA (9) · KO (6) · OB (4) · OK (6) · OU (2) · PO (4) · ST (2) · TE (2) · UG (3) · UR (2) · YU (5) · ZO (11)</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy: Using 2-Letter Words Effectively</h2>

      <p>Knowing the words is only half the battle. The real skill lies in applying them to create high-scoring plays. Here are the key techniques that separate beginners from advanced players.</p>

      <!-- Purple Strategy Tips -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel plays:</span> Place your word alongside an existing word so every adjacent pair forms a valid 2-letter word. A single parallel play can score 30–50 points by forming 3–4 words simultaneously.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hook plays:</span> Add a single letter to an existing word to create a new 2-letter word perpendicular to it. For example, adding a Q next to an I already on the board creates QI for 11 points plus whatever your main word scores.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Dump difficult tiles:</span> Words like JO, KA, QI, XI, XU, and ZA let you offload high-value tiles that are otherwise hard to use. Playing QI is almost always better than holding the Q hoping for a longer word.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Premium square access:</span> Short words let you reach premium squares that longer words cannot. A 2-letter word placed on a Triple Word Score still triples your total — and the perpendicular words formed count too.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Tight board control:</span> In defensive games, 2-letter words let you score without opening up the board. Play parallel to existing words in cramped areas where your opponent cannot extend.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Comparison Cards -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Smart 2-Letter Use</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Play QI on a DL/TL square for 22–33 points. Form parallel plays scoring 3+ words at once. Use ZA to dump the Z early and keep your rack flexible.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Common Mistakes</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Holding the Q for a long word (usually costs you points). Not knowing obscure 2-letter words and missing parallel opportunities. Playing 2-letter words that open Triple Word squares for opponents.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

